Description: Decorated limestone ostracon: inscribed with the name of Ramses VI (?). On one side only, below a text in eleven columns and a drawing of a crocodile in black; the tail is missing.
Curator's comments: Bibliography: S. Birch, 'Inscriptions in the Hieratic and Demotic Character from the Collections of the British Museum' (London, 1868), pl. IV.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (393220) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/393220)
